post_text:
IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT
The Department of Agriculture (USDA) announced earlier this week that beginning September 1st schools will be allowed to serve ALL students free meals temporarily “as long as funding allows.” This will also include grab and go breakfast (offered to middle school and high school students) and the first slice of pizza. We will continue to offer a-la carte items. Extra milk or juice will be charged $.50 each and extra pizza will be charged $2.50 per slice. All monies previously paid to your child’s account will remain as a credit in their account for future use. Please feel free to contact me with any further questions at (405) 964-5558.
Mrs. Johnny Radford
Cafeteria Manager

If you are a new student living in the Dale School District, you can complete enrollment papers beginning Monday, August 3 from 9-11 and 1-3. You’ll need to bring the following items:
Birth certificate
Up-to-date shot record

Custody Agreement and

Incoming Dale 6th grade parents/students:
Now is the time to get signed up for band! Hopefully by this point, you have received a letter with important information about our band program. Nick Noble
Band Director
Dale Public School

post_text: Superintendent Charlie Dickinson has announced his retirement from Dale Public Schools. His leadership skills and administrative knowledge will be greatly missed. His most famous saying is, “We’ll do what is best for the kids.” Mr. Dickinson has been in education for 40 years. 39 of those years have been at Dale serving as Dale Baseball Coach, Science Teacher, Elementary Principal, and Superintendent. Good Luck and God Bless as you enjoy the fruits of your labor.

post_text:
Oklahoma’s Promise: Alert for 10th grade parents with recent income loss-
If your student was in the 10th grade during school year 2019-2020 and you anticipate that your 2020 income may be under the $55,000 application limit for the Oklahoma’s Promise scholarship due to recent reductions in your income, you may submit an application based on your estimated 2020 income. The application must be submitted prior to the June 30, 2020, deadline. You will be required to provide a copy of your 2020 federal income tax return when completed to verify that your income was under $55,000. The application will be held as pending until the tax documentation is received. Please send any questions to okpromise@osrhe.edu

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT ABOUT CLEANING OUT LOCKERS-
We will adhere to the following schedule:
Wednesday, May 6
12th grade and 6th grade may come up from 9:00 am-11:00 am
Wednesday, May 6
11th grade and 7th grade may
come up from 12:30 pm-2:30 pm
Thursday, May 7
10th grade and 8th grade may
come up from 9:00 am-11:00 am
Thursday, May 7
9th grade may come up from 12:30-2:30 pm

You may also clean out athletic lockers in the gym and ball fields. Band students may pick up and/or return instruments at this time. It will be helpful to scatter these times and not have everyone arrive right at 9:00 or 12:30. Your help and cooperation is appreciated.

Students do not have to be in the vehicle. For safety of all involved, no walk ups will be allowed, and you’ll need to remain in your vehicle at all times.

Concurrrnt Enrollment for next year- If you are a junior that plans to go concurrent next year, there are some new guidelines:
1. The colleges will accept an email from the counselor in lieu of documents that have to be signed.
2. If you don’t have an ACT score that meets admissions standards, they will accept an alternative method. At this time, I don’t know what that method will be, but perhaps you can ask them that question. If you already have an ACT score that is acceptable, you’re fine.
3. You can call 405-382-9751 for more information. This is the number for SSC, but she can answer a generic question.
4. My email: ccantrell@dale.k12.ok.us
